# Universal Code Style

## Line Length

- Hard limit: **100 columns** for all languages.
- Python: enforced by `ruff` (`line-length = 100` in `pyproject.toml`).
- C++: enforced by `clang-format` (`ColumnLimit: 100`).
- SQL: enforced by `sqlfluff` (`max_line_length = 100`).
- Markdown / YAML: soft limit — prefer wrapping at 100 but do not break URLs or code spans.

## Naming Conventions by Language

| Language | Variables / functions | Classes / types | Constants | Modules / files |
|----------|-----------------------|-----------------|-----------|-----------------|
| Python | `snake_case` | `PascalCase` | `UPPER_SNAKE_CASE` | `snake_case.py` |
| C++ | `snake_case` | `PascalCase` | `kPascalCase` | `snake_case.cpp/.h` |
| JavaScript / Jinja macros | `lowerCamelCase` | `PascalCase` | `UPPER_SNAKE_CASE` | `kebab-case.js` |
| SQL | `snake_case` | n/a | n/a | `snake_case.sql` |
| YAML / TOML keys | `snake_case` or `kebab-case` (match existing file convention) | | | |

## Whitespace

- No trailing whitespace on any line.
- Files must end with exactly one newline (`\n`).
- No mixed tabs and spaces — Python: 4 spaces; C++: 4 spaces; YAML/TOML: 2 spaces.
- Enforced by pre-commit `trailing-whitespace` and `end-of-file-fixer` hooks.

## Imports & Includes

- Python: `ruff` isort profile — stdlib → third-party → first-party (`zinc`, service name).
- C++: own header first, then stdlib, then third-party, then project headers.
- Never use wildcard imports (`from foo import *`).
- Never use `using namespace std;` in C++ headers.

## Comments

- Comments explain **why**, not what — the code says what.
- No commented-out code in commits. Use `git stash` or a branch.
- `TODO` comments must include a linked issue: `# TODO(#42): description`.
- Doxygen blocks on all public C++ symbols; Google-style docstrings on all public Python symbols.

## Commit Messages

Follow [Conventional Commits](https://www.conventionalcommits.org/):

```
<type>(<scope>): <subject>

[optional body]

[optional footer: Refs #issue]
```

- **Types:** `feat`, `fix`, `chore`, `docs`, `test`, `refactor`, `perf`, `ci`, `build`
- Subject: imperative mood, lowercase, no trailing period, ≤ 72 chars
- No merge commits on `main` — squash-merge PRs
- No secrets, credentials, or PII in commit messages

## Files the AI Must Never Modify Without Asking

- `audit_log` migrations (append-only schema)
- `.env` / `.env.*` files in any directory
- `secrets/` directory contents
- `CLAUDE.md` (prompt this rule file to update it)
